<div class="assistant-text"><h2>ChromDetect Project Overview</h2>
<p><strong>ChromDetect</strong> is a Python bioinformatics tool that detects and classifies chromosome-level scaffolds in genome assemblies. It solves a common problem in genomics: different assembly pipelines use inconsistent naming conventions (e.g., <code>chr1</code>, <code>Super_scaffold_1</code>, <code>SUPER_1</code>, <code>LG_1</code>, NCBI accessions, etc.).</p>
<h3>Project Structure</h3>
<pre><code>chromdetect/
├── chromdetect/           # Main package (807 lines)
│   ├── __init__.py        # Public API exports
│   ├── core.py            # Core classification logic (463 lines)
│   ├── patterns.py        # Regex pattern definitions (99 lines)
│   └── cli.py             # Command-line interface (215 lines)
├── tests/                 # Test suite (560 lines)
├── examples/              # Usage examples
└── .github/workflows/     # CI/CD (test + publish)
</code></pre>
<h3>Key Features</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Pattern-based detection</strong>: 15+ regex patterns for chromosome naming conventions</li>
<li><strong>Size-based detection</strong>: Heuristics using N50, scaffold size ratios</li>
<li><strong>Karyotype refinement</strong>: Adjusts classification based on expected chromosome count</li>
<li><strong>Multiple output formats</strong>: JSON, TSV, human-readable summary</li>
<li><strong>Pure Python</strong>: Zero runtime dependencies, Python 3.9+</li>
</ul>
<h3>Architecture Flow</h3>
<ol>
<li><strong>Input</strong>: FASTA file (plain or gzipped)</li>
<li><strong>Parsing</strong>: <code>parse_fasta()</code> → scaffold names, lengths, sequence samples</li>
<li><strong>Classification</strong>: <code>classify_scaffolds()</code> → combines name + size detection</li>
<li><strong>Output</strong>: <code>ScaffoldInfo</code> objects + <code>AssemblyStats</code> + formatted results</li>
</ol>
<h3>Usage</h3>
<p><strong>CLI:</strong></p>
<pre><code class="language-bash">chromdetect assembly.fasta --format json --karyotype 24
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Python API:</strong></p>
<pre><code class="language-python">from chromdetect import parse_fasta, classify_scaffolds
scaffolds = parse_fasta(&quot;assembly.fasta.gz&quot;)
results, stats = classify_scaffolds(scaffolds, expected_chromosomes=24)
</code></pre>
<h3>Development</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Build</strong>: <code>pip install -e ".[dev]"</code></li>
<li><strong>Test</strong>: <code>pytest</code> (tests Python 3.9-3.12)</li>
<li><strong>Lint</strong>: <code>ruff check chromdetect</code></li>
<li><strong>Type check</strong>: <code>mypy chromdetect</code></li>
</ul>
<p>The project is well-structured with strict type checking, comprehensive tests, and modern Python packaging. Version 0.1.0 (Beta), MIT licensed.</p></div></div></div>
