    14→- `Super_scaffold_1`, `Superscaffold_1`, `SUPER_1`
    15→- `chr1`, `chromosome_1`, `Chr_1`
    16→- `LG_1` (linkage groups)
    17→- `scaffold_1_cov50` (coverage-annotated)
    18→- `HiC_scaffold_1`, `Scaffold_1_RaGOO`
    19→- `NC_000001.11`, `CM000001.1` (NCBI accessions)
    20→
    21→This inconsistency makes automated analysis and cross-species comparisons difficult. Existing QC tools like QUAST report metrics but don&#x27;t classify scaffolds. Scaffolding tools like LACHESIS create assemblies but don&#x27;t help interpret existing ones.
    22→
    23→## The Solution
    24→
    25→ChromDetect uses multiple complementary strategies to identify chromosome-level scaffolds:
    26→
    27→1. **Name-based detection** - Regex patterns for 15+ common naming conventions
    28→2. **Size-based detection** - Large scaffolds are typically chromosomes
    29→3. **N50-based detection** - Scaffolds contributing to N50 are typically chromosome-level
    30→4. **Karyotype-informed detection** - Use known chromosome count to adjust classifications
    31→
    32→## Installation
    33→
    34→```bash
    35→pip install chromdetect
    36→```
    37→
    38→Or install from source:
    39→
    40→```bash
    41→git clone https://github.com/verity-project/chromdetect.git
    42→cd chromdetect
    43→pip install -e .
    44→```
    45→
    46→## Quick Start
    47→
    48→### Command Line
    49→
    50→```bash
    51→# Basic usage - get summary
    52→chromdetect assembly.fasta
    53→
    54→# Output JSON for programmatic use
    55→chromdetect assembly.fasta --format json --output results.json
    56→
    57→# Use karyotype information for better accuracy
    58→chromdetect assembly.fasta --karyotype 24
    59→
    60→# Export only chromosome-level scaffolds as TSV
    61→chromdetect assembly.fasta --chromosomes-only --format tsv &gt; chromosomes.tsv
    62→```
    63→
    64→### Python API
    65→
    66→```python
    67→from chromdetect import parse_fasta, classify_scaffolds
    68→
    69→# Parse and classify
    70→scaffolds = parse_fasta(&quot;assembly.fasta.gz&quot;)
    71→results, stats = classify_scaffolds(scaffolds, expected_chromosomes=24)
    72→
    73→# Print summary
    74→print(f&quot;Found {stats.chromosome_count} chromosomes&quot;)
    75→print(f&quot;Total assembly: {stats.total_length / 1e9:.2f} Gb&quot;)
    76→print(f&quot;N50: {stats.n50 / 1e6:.1f} Mb&quot;)
    77→
    78→# Access individual scaffold classifications
    79→for r in results:
    80→    if r.classification == &quot;chromosome&quot;:
    81→        print(f&quot;{r.name}: {r.length:,} bp (confidence: {r.confidence:.2f})&quot;)
    82→```
    83→
    84→## Output Formats
    85→
    86→### Summary (default)
    87→
    88→```
    89→============================================================
    90→CHROMDETECT ASSEMBLY ANALYSIS
    91→============================================================
    92→
    93→Total scaffolds:     1,234
    94→Total length:        2,876,543,210 bp (2.88 Gb)
    95→N50:                 45,678,901 bp (45.7 Mb)
    96→N90:                 12,345,678 bp
    97→Largest scaffold:    198,765,432 bp
    98→
    99→Scaffold Classification:
   100→  Chromosomes:       24 (2.85 Gb)
   101→  Unlocalized:       15
   102→  Unplaced:          1,195
   103→
   104→Chromosome N50:      118,234,567 bp (118.2 Mb)
   105→GC content:          41.2%
   106→```
   107→
   108→### JSON
   109→
   110→```json
   111→{
   112→  &quot;summary&quot;: {
   113→    &quot;total_scaffolds&quot;: 1234,
   114→    &quot;chromosome_count&quot;: 24,
   115→    &quot;n50&quot;: 45678901,
   116→    ...
   117→  },
   118→  &quot;scaffolds&quot;: [
   119→    {
   120→      &quot;name&quot;: &quot;chr1&quot;,
   121→      &quot;length&quot;: 198765432,
   122→      &quot;classification&quot;: &quot;chromosome&quot;,
   123→      &quot;confidence&quot;: 0.95,
   124→      &quot;detection_method&quot;: &quot;name_chr_explicit&quot;,
   125→      &quot;chromosome_id&quot;: &quot;1&quot;
   126→    },
   127→    ...
   128→  ]
   129→}
   130→```
   131→
   132→### TSV
   133→
   134→```
   135→name    length    classification    confidence    method    chromosome_id
   136→chr1    198765432    chromosome    0.95    name_chr_explicit    1
   137→chr2    175432198    chromosome    0.93    name_chr_explicit    2
   138→...
   139→```
   140→
   141→## Options
   142→
   143→| Option | Description |
   144→|--------|-------------|
   145→| `-f, --format` | Output format: `summary`, `json`, `tsv` (default: summary) |
   146→| `-o, --output` | Write output to file instead of stdout |
   147→| `-k, --karyotype` | Expected chromosome count for karyotype-informed detection |
   148→| `-s, --min-size` | Minimum size (bp) to consider chromosome-level (default: 10Mb) |
   149→| `-c, --chromosomes-only` | Only output chromosome-level scaffolds |
   150→| `-q, --quiet` | Suppress progress messages |
   151→
   152→## Supported Naming Conventions
   153→
   154→ChromDetect recognizes these naming patterns (case-insensitive):
   155→
   156→| Pattern | Examples | Method |
   157→|---------|----------|--------|
   158→| Explicit chromosome | `chr1`, `chromosome_X`, `Chr_MT` | `name_chr_explicit` |
   159→| Super scaffold | `Super_scaffold_1`, `Superscaffold_X` | `name_super_scaffold` |
   160→| SUPER | `SUPER_1`, `SUPER1` | `name_SUPER` |
   161→| Linkage group | `LG1`, `LG_X` | `name_linkage_group` |
   162→| NCBI RefSeq | `NC_000001.11` | `name_ncbi_refseq` |
   163→| NCBI GenBank | `CM000001.1` | `name_ncbi_genbank` |
   164→| HiC scaffold | `HiC_scaffold_1` | `name_hic_scaffold` |
   165→| RaGOO | `Scaffold_1_RaGOO` | `name_ragoo` |
   166→| Simple numeric | `1`, `X`, `MT` | `name_numeric` |
   167→
   168→Patterns that indicate **unlocalized** scaffolds:
   169→- `*_random`, `*_unloc*`, `chrUn_*`
   170→
   171→Patterns that indicate **unplaced** scaffolds (contigs/fragments):
   172→- `*_ctg*`, `*contig*`, `*_arrow_*`, `*_pilon*`, `*_hap*`
   173→
   174→## How It Works
   175→
   176→ChromDetect combines name-based and size-based detection with these priority rules:
   177→
   178→1. **Strong name match (confidence ≥ 0.8)** takes priority
   179→2. **Large scaffold + weak name match** = chromosome with boosted confidence
   180→3. **Large scaffold + no name match** = chromosome with reduced confidence
   181→4. **Small scaffold** = unplaced regardless of name
   182→
   183→When `--karyotype` is provided:
   184→- If too many candidates: demote lowest-confidence chromosomes
   185→- If too few candidates: promote largest unplaced scaffolds
   186→
   187→## Use Cases
   188→
   189→### VGP Assembly Validation
   190→
   191→```bash
   192→# Validate a VGP curated assembly
   193→chromdetect species.pri.cur.fasta.gz --karyotype 24 --format json
   194→```
   195→
   196→### Cross-Species Comparison
   197→
   198→```python
   199→from chromdetect import parse_fasta, classify_scaffolds
   200→
   201→species_files = [&quot;human.fa&quot;, &quot;mouse.fa&quot;, &quot;zebrafish.fa&quot;]
   202→karyotypes = [23, 20, 25]
   203→
   204→for fasta, n_chr in zip(species_files, karyotypes):
   205→    scaffolds = parse_fasta(fasta)
   206→    results, stats = classify_scaffolds(scaffolds, expected_chromosomes=n_chr)
   207→    print(f&quot;{fasta}: {stats.chromosome_count} chromosomes detected&quot;)
   208→```
   209→
   210→### Pipeline Integration
   211→
   212→```bash
   213→# As part of assembly QC pipeline
   214→chromdetect assembly.fasta --format json | jq &#x27;.summary.chromosome_count&#x27;
   215→```
   216→
   217→## Contributing
   218→
   219→Contributions are welcome! Please see [CONTRIBUTING.md](CONTRIBUTING.md) for guidelines.
   220→
   221→### Adding New Patterns
   222→
   223→To add support for a new naming convention:
   224→
   225→1. Add the regex pattern to `chromdetect/patterns.py`
   226→2. Include a descriptive method name
   227→3. Ensure the pattern captures chromosome ID in group 1
   228→4. Add tests in `tests/test_patterns.py`
   229→
   230→Example:
   231→
   232→```python
   233→# In patterns.py
   234→CHROMOSOME_PATTERNS.append(
   235→    (r&#x27;^MyConvention_(\d+)$&#x27;, &#x27;my_convention&#x27;),
   236→)
   237→```
   238→
   239→## Citation
   240→
   241→If you use ChromDetect in your research, please cite:
   242→
   243→```
   244→ChromDetect: Chromosome-level scaffold detection for genome assemblies
   245→https://github.com/verity-project/chromdetect
   246→```
